text:
541-533 East 79th Street, at, adjoining, and west of the N.W. corner of East End Avenue, also showing 2-10 East End Avenue.

About 1912.

East End Avenue east side, north from 79th Street.
August 2, 1927.
P.L. Sperr,Photographer.

South end of East End Avenue at 79th Street, showing in background E. M. Schwartz factory.

P.L. Sperr, Photographer.
August 2, 1927.

Marie Curie Ave., (waters edge) north from East 78th (left) to East 81st (right) Streets, showing several apartments lining the East River. Intersection in the center is 79th Street with East End Ave.; starting there. The edifice on the extreme left is the Junior League Residential Club.

1930.

Ewing Galloway.

(1)
East River, north from East 76th (left) to East 80th Streets, showing John Jay Park, the East End Hotel for Women, and (extreme right) the 14-story apartment house No. 1 East End Ave., from East 79th to East 80th Streets.
April 5, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, including a view of East 79th Street, west from Exterior Street (Marie Curie Ave.), and the 15-story apartment house, the Yorkgate, No. 25 East End Ave., at the S.E. corner of East 80th Street.
April 5, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same, as No. 1, at a later date.
Autumn 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
